====================================================
ServiceNow – Overview (Exam Notes)
====================================================

----------------------------------------------------
1. What is ServiceNow?
----------------------------------------------------
- ServiceNow is a cloud-based enterprise platform.
- It provides a single system of record to automate business processes.
- Used to manage IT services and other enterprise workflows.
- Delivered as Platform as a Service (PaaS).

----------------------------------------------------
2. Why ServiceNow? (Key Reasons)
----------------------------------------------------

2.1 Customization and Flexibility
- Offers high level of customization.
- Platform can be tailored to match enterprise goals.
- Supports custom workflows, forms, and processes.

2.2 Seamless Integrations
- Integrates easily with third-party tools and platforms.
- Helps centralize data and workflows.
- Improves visibility and operational control.

2.3 Cognitive AI Capabilities
- Uses AI for predictive and advanced experiences.
- Helps predict issues and automate solutions.
- Improves customer experience and saves time.

2.4 Robust Security
- Strong security features to protect data and processes.
- Protects against cyber threats.
- Ensures data confidentiality and integrity.

2.5 Community Support
- Active ServiceNow community.
- Users share solutions, experiences, and best practices.
- Provides extensive learning and documentation resources.

2.6 Continual Service Improvement (CSI)
- Supports continuous monitoring and improvement.
- Helps analyze and optimize operations over time.
- Core principle of ServiceNow platform.

----------------------------------------------------
3. Benefits of ServiceNow
----------------------------------------------------

3.1 Streamlined Workflows
- Reduces complexity of business processes.
- Improves efficiency through automation.

3.2 Scalability
- Cloud-based and highly scalable.
- Supports business growth without infrastructure concerns.

3.3 Automation
- Automates repetitive and manual tasks.
- Allows focus on strategic initiatives.

3.4 Improved Service Delivery
- Enhances service quality.
- Improves customer satisfaction and loyalty.

3.5 Risk Mitigation
- Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC) capabilities.
- Helps meet industry regulations and standards.

3.6 Lower Operational Costs
- Automation reduces manual effort.
- Improves operational efficiency and cost savings.

3.7 Real-Time Analytics and Dashboards
- Provides real-time reporting and dashboards.
- Enables quick and informed decision-making.

----------------------------------------------------
4. ServiceNow Platform
----------------------------------------------------
- ServiceNow is an American company.
- Its product is known as the ServiceNow Platform.
- Provides a single platform for enterprise automation.
- Used across the entire organization.

4.1 Enterprise Usage Areas
- IT Service Management (ITSM)
- Human Resources (HR)
- Asset Management
- Operations Management
- Customer Service Management (CSM)
- And many other enterprise functions

4.2 AI and Automation
- Built-in automation for daily tasks.
- Provides default workflows and configurations.
- Includes modules for common business operations.

4.3 Well-Integrated Platform
- Connects with other systems seamlessly.
- Ensures scalability, security, and reliability.
- Supports governance models when used effectively.

----------------------------------------------------
5. ServiceNow Architecture
----------------------------------------------------

5.1 Cloud-Based Architecture
- Hosted and maintained by ServiceNow.
- Accessed via internet using web browsers.

5.2 Multi-Instance Architecture
- Each customer gets a dedicated instance.
- Data, applications, and customizations are isolated.
- Multiple instances can exist per organization.
- Instances can communicate securely if required.

5.3 Single Data Model
- Uses a single, unified data model.
- Built on flexible table schema.
- Provides reusable core components.

5.4 High Availability Data Centers
- Uses redundant and geographically distributed data centers.
- Traffic is rerouted automatically during failures.
- Ensures continuous availability.

5.5 Backup and Cloning
- Four weekly full backups.
- Six days of daily differential backups.
- Backups used for data restoration.
- Used in instance cloning (lower instances copied from production).

----------------------------------------------------
6. Supported Browsers
----------------------------------------------------
- ServiceNow is accessed via web browsers.
- User logs in using company-provided instance URL.
- After login, users can navigate the instance UI.

6.1 Supported Browsers
- Google Chrome
- Microsoft Edge
- Mozilla Firefox
- Apple Safari

----------------------------------------------------
7. Session Summary
----------------------------------------------------
- Covered ServiceNow overview.
- Discussed:
  - Why ServiceNow
  - Benefits
  - Platform
  - Architecture
  - Supported browsers
- Next topic: ServiceNow User Interface and Navigation.

====================================================
End of Notes
====================================================





# ServiceNow CSA 2025 – MCQs + Final Revision

====================================================
SECTION 1: CSA PRACTICE MCQs
====================================================

Q1. What type of cloud service does ServiceNow provide?
A. Software as a Service (SaaS)
B. Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS)
C. Platform as a Service (PaaS)
D. Database as a Service

✔ Answer: Platform as a Service (PaaS)
Explanation: ServiceNow provides a platform to build and run enterprise applications.

----------------------------------------------------

Q2. How is ServiceNow delivered to users?
A. Installed on local machines
B. Accessed through desktop application
C. Accessed through web browsers
D. Via mobile app only

✔ Answer: Accessed through web browsers
Explanation: ServiceNow is cloud-based and accessed using supported browsers.

----------------------------------------------------

Q3. Which architecture does ServiceNow use?
A. Multi-tenant architecture
B. Single-instance architecture
C. Multi-instance architecture
D. Peer-to-peer architecture

✔ Answer: Multi-instance architecture
Explanation: Each customer gets a dedicated, isolated instance.

----------------------------------------------------

Q4. In ServiceNow, what is an instance?
A. A user account
B. A database table
C. A dedicated software stack for a customer
D. A workflow

✔ Answer: A dedicated software stack for a customer
Explanation: Instance contains customer data, applications, and configurations.

----------------------------------------------------

Q5. Which of the following is TRUE about ServiceNow instances?
A. All customers share the same database
B. Customizations affect other customers
C. Instances are isolated from each other
D. Only one instance per ServiceNow customer

✔ Answer: Instances are isolated from each other
Explanation: Isolation ensures security and stability.

----------------------------------------------------

Q6. ServiceNow is primarily used for:
A. Gaming applications
B. Social networking
C. Enterprise service management
D. Graphic design

✔ Answer: Enterprise service management
Explanation: ServiceNow automates enterprise workflows.

----------------------------------------------------

Q7. Which module is NOT commonly supported by ServiceNow?
A. IT Service Management
B. HR Service Delivery
C. Customer Service Management
D. Video Editing Management

✔ Answer: Video Editing Management
Explanation: ServiceNow supports enterprise workflows, not media tools.

----------------------------------------------------

Q8. What enables automation of repetitive tasks in ServiceNow?
A. Manual scripts
B. Cognitive AI and workflows
C. External databases
D. Browser extensions

✔ Answer: Cognitive AI and workflows
Explanation: Automation is core to the platform.

----------------------------------------------------

Q9. Which feature helps during system failure?
A. UI Policies
B. High Availability Data Centers
C. Forms
D. Client Scripts

✔ Answer: High Availability Data Centers
Explanation: Traffic is rerouted automatically during failures.

----------------------------------------------------

Q10. Backups in ServiceNow are mainly used for:
A. Performance tuning
B. UI customization
C. Data restoration and cloning
D. User authentication

✔ Answer: Data restoration and cloning
Explanation: Backups help restore data and clone instances.

----------------------------------------------------

Q11. Which browser is NOT supported by ServiceNow?
A. Google Chrome
B. Mozilla Firefox
C. Internet Explorer
D. Microsoft Edge

✔ Answer: Internet Explorer
Explanation: IE is deprecated and unsupported.

----------------------------------------------------

Q12. What is the purpose of a single data model in ServiceNow?
A. To restrict customization
B. To unify data and reuse components
C. To reduce security
D. To limit integrations

✔ Answer: To unify data and reuse components
Explanation: Single data model improves consistency and reusability.

====================================================
END OF CSA 2025 NOTES
====================================================
